Hewlett Packard Co Wins Court Ruling In Itanium Litigation With Oracle Corp
Wednesday, 1 Aug 2012 04:22pm EDT
Hewlett Packard Co announced that the Court ordered and declared as follows: In this action for declaratory relief, the Court finds in favor of HP and against Oracle on both the breach of contract and promissory estoppel causes of action brought by HP; The Settlement and Release Agreement entered into by HP, Oracle and Hurd on September 20, 2010, requires Oracle to continue to offer its product suite on HP's Itanium-based server platforms and does not confer on Oracle the discretion to decide whether to do so or not; The terms "product suite" means Oracle software products that were offered on HP's Itanium-based servers at the time Oracle signed the September 20, 2010 Settlement and Release Agreement, including any new releases, versions or updates of those products; Oracle's obligation to continue to offer its products on HP's Itanium-based server platforms lasts until such time as HP discontinues the sales of its Itanium-based servers; Oracle is required to port its products to HP's Itanium-based servers without charge to HP.Â 
